Real Madrid have submitted a final offer to Erling Haaland’s entourage as they look to sign the Borussia Dortmund star, according to reports. The La Liga titans’ interest in Kylian Mbappe has been well-documented. Yet with a deal for the France international far from guaranteed, club president Florentino Perez has now decided to take action. Real Madrid have seen Karim Benzema continue to shine this term, with the 34-year-old scoring 22 goals in the Champions League and La Liga combined. However, with the veteran approaching the twilight years of his career, Los Blancos are looking at long-term replacements. Real Madrid Target Mauricio Pochettino Ancelotti’s Future At Madrid Hangs In Balance It’s an open secret Madrid want to sign Mbappe, who scored the winner against them for Paris Saint-Germain in the Champions League on Tuesday night. Yet they’re also in the mix when it comes to landing Haaland as Perez plots yet another Galactico era. Now, Catalan newspaper Sport say Real Madrid have submitted a ‘final offer’ when it comes to landing Haaland. That has been sent to his entourage, with the striker currently represented by controversial figure Mino Raiola. The report says Madrid have ‘accelerated’ their plans because of Mbappe, with the La Liga side aware of his current stance. POLL They’ve also rocked Barcelona and Manchester City in the process, with the two European giants also in the frame to sign Haaland. Madrid are said to believe that Haaland and Mbappe can help them dominate world football for the best part of a decade. And they’re confident they will soon have an agreement with the striker, who has scored 16 goals from 14 Bundesliga games. The 21-year-old has also struck four times in the DFB-Pokal and three times in the Champions League, too. Haaland and Mbappe could make Real a force to be reckoned with once again.